caption: Fairly new to DC and have been making the rounds of the numerous sushi restaurants. So far, Young Chow on Capitol Hill is one of my favs! It's so good! The pic is the Sushi and Sashimi dinner. The best part is that their Chinese menu is just as good as their sushi menu so the rest of my family can  eat too! My daughter loved the Peking Duck and the Mango Chicken. Husband has so far enjoyed the szechuan chicken and the egg rolls. For now we've only had take out, but I'm looking forward to dining in soon one day.

Food was disappointing and disgusting. Pai Thai was sour like spoiled(taste and smell) and the lemongrass chicken is swimming in sauce, never grilled in the restaurant,definitely sous vide, accompanied by overcooked vegetables on a skewer that also never saw a grill.

We love to go out. Last night we went to this magnificent place which we didn’t know before. We had a delightful evening there with high-qulity dishes and a courteous stuff and a great cook. We put this fine restaurant in our list  and we shall surely come back very soon. We deeply recommend.
Young Chow will always be my go-to-Chinese spot here in DC. Food is great and so is customer service. With the pandemic, I'm still a regular and they do free delivery!
Shrimp broccoli plenty of shirmp ,friendly hot food but the sauce was really watery u can taste the sugar i used to thick sauce that was a small issue

Food is great, however didn't had any utensils in the bag. Shouldn't be something that I had to ask for, it should already in the bag. But the food and service was amazing! Salmon lover entree is the best !! Definitely check it out!
Been frequenting this place for over 10 years. Always consistent and great quality. Love the food and nice atmosphere.
Very slow service. I been waiting for an hour for a order
I really liked their food. I always get fantastic service here. The place is clean and the employees are always nice. Will visit here again.

We ordered vegetarian sushi and veg General Tso's - everything was really good. Well made and ready on time. They packaged the General Tso's in a way that didn't let it get soggy on the drive home. Looking forward to pickup from here again!
Great classic Chinese food! Large portions, great vegetarian options, delicious food!

It took awhile but I finally found my favorite spot for Chinese food in Capitol Hill. My favorite dishes are the orange chicken and shrimp lo mein. They also have a lot of good boba options and their lunch combos are good. They also have a diverse menu and are quick to complete your order. The staff is also friendly, there is one lady who always (pre-COVID) offered me a cup of tea and a seat while I waited to pick up my order. I only wish their delivery area was larger. Hopefully after the pandemic I will get to try a drink at the bar.
Americanized. Not authentic. Taste like your neighborhood Chinese food not Thai
